                <h2 class="txt-gold">The Judging Process</h2>
                <p>The adjudication process is completely independent and is comprised of a panel of 7 judges who represent different areas of the business and entrepreneurship communities.</p>
                <p>The evaluation process runs through 5 different filtering stages, which ensure that all entries and information contained is checked and rechecked to remove human error and subjectivity.</p>
                <p><span class="txt-gold sub-intro-head uptxt">Stage 1:</span><br />Preliminary screening of the entry forms to shortlist and arrange them according to the respective award categories, this only happens once they have met all the minimum entry criterion and competition rules. </p>
                <p><span class="txt-gold sub-intro-head uptxt">Stage 2:</span><br />Compiled forms will be sent through to the judges for preliminary adjudication and assessment.</p>
                <p><span class="txt-gold sub-intro-head uptxt">Stage 3:</span><br />Post the preliminary assessment, 5 finalists will be chosen for each of the 10 categories and they will be required to do an online/ telephonic interview with our panel of judges.</p>
                <p><span class="txt-gold sub-intro-head uptxt">Stage 4:</span><br />Due diligence will then be done on each of the finalists, post this process the judges will then select a winner and runner ups for each of the categories.</p>
                <p><span class="txt-gold sub-intro-head uptxt">Stage 5:</span><br />From the 10 award category winners our judges will then further adjudicate in order to determine the winner of the coveted Maverick Start-Up of The Year and Maverick of The Year Award winner, which is the ultimate and most prestigious category.</p>
                <p>NB: At any stage during the adjudication stages financial information and other supporting documents may be requested by our judges. The data would be requested in order to give the judges critical information which they need in order to make a complete and holistic assessment on the entrepreneur being reviewed and when it is required, entrepreneurs are urged to promptly supply it in order not to delay the judging process.</p>
